to our patients, employees and investors; \nR - Respect for all: To recognize the contribution of every employee and respect the rights and the dignity of every patient and employee; \nE - Excellence: To create a culture of ensuring the highest quality of consistent and reliable services to our patients and sustainable value for our stakeholders. \n\nWhat makes Narayana Health different?\n\n- More than 1,07,000 Cardiac Surgeries till 2014\n- Amongst the largest telemedicine networks in the world\n- Largest in the world - 80 bedded dedicated post-op pediatric cardiac ICU in NH, Bangalore\n- Patients from 77 countries\n- One of the largest dialysis units in India with 217 dedicated beds & 1,30,000 procedures per year\n-  Largest  Bone Marrow Transplant Unit (14 bedded) in India\n- 2 JCI accredited hospitals\n- 4 NABH accredited hospitals\n- More than 1800 full time doctors \n\n::: CSR Initiatives :::\n\nAt NH, CSR is ingrained in our DNA. We work closely with government to fund poor patients, few such initiatives include:\n\n* Udayer Pathe: Incentives for aspiring doctors (children studying in 7th Std.) in WestBengal.\n\n* Yeshaswini Micro- Health Insurance Scheme: Worlds largest self funded scheme covering more than 3million farmers & their families in Karnataka for all surgical procedures & outpatient care.   \n\nWe at Narayana Health have a dream! - \"A dream of making quality healthcare available to the masses worldwide\".\n\n::: Narayana Health Group of Hospitals :::\n\nAhmedabad, Narayana Multispeciality Hospital\t079 - 71222222\nBangalore, Narayana Institute of Cardiac Sciences 080 -71222222\nBangalore, Mazumdar Shaw Medical Center\t080 -71222222\nBangalore, Chinmaya Narayana Superspeciality Centre\t080 -25200001\nBangalore, MS Ramaiah Narayana Heart Centre\t080 -22183078\nBangalore, St. Martha's Heart Centre\t9538043453\nBangalore, Suguna Narayana Heart Centre\t8884431622\nBangalore, Whitefield, Narayana Multispeciality Hospital \n080 -71112555\nBangalore, HSR